{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD"]]},"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"SwiftUI Integration","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"FlyHUD"}]},"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/swiftui-integration","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/advanced-features","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/custom-ui","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/best-practices","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/testing"],"generated":true,"title":"Guides"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/flyhud\/swiftui-integration"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provides a native SwiftUI API on top of FlyHUD’s UIKit core. It offers four levels of abstraction:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Layer"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use Case","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bridge"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudHost($hostView)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Direct UIKit-style control","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Declarative","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":".hud(isPresented:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".hud(item:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".hudStatus(isPresented:)","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Binding-driven state management","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Convenience","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":".hudLoading()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".hudToast()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".hudProgress()","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Common presets with minimal setup","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Liquid Glass","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"code":".hudGlass()","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS 26+ translucent glass style","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All APIs support iOS 13+, tvOS 13+, and visionOS 1.0+.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Architecture","level":3,"anchor":"Architecture","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following diagram shows the layered architecture and how each public API flows through internal components to the UIKit core:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"swiftui-architecture.svg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"How It Works","level":3,"anchor":"How-It-Works","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following diagram shows the interaction flow between SwiftUI bindings and the UIKit HUD:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"swiftui-bridge.svg"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Installation","level":2,"anchor":"Installation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI"},{"text":" to your package dependencies:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/liam-i\/FlyHUD.git\", from: \"1.7.0\")","],","targets: [","    .target(","        name: \"MyTarget\",","        dependencies: [","            .product(name: \"FlyHUDSwiftUI\", package: \"FlyHUD\")","        ]","    )","]"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Or in Xcode: File → Add Package Dependencies → select ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" depends on ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" automatically. You only need to add ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyIndicatorHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyProgressHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you use custom indicator\/progress styles.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"text":"Import","level":2,"anchor":"Import","type":"heading"},{"code":["import FlyHUDSwiftUI","","\/\/ Optional — for custom indicator styles","import FlyIndicatorHUD","","\/\/ Optional — for custom progress styles","import FlyProgressHUD"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Layer 1: UIKit Bridge","level":2,"anchor":"Layer-1-UIKit-Bridge","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For maximum control, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudHost()"},{"text":" to obtain a backing UIView, then call UIKit APIs directly:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct MyView: View {","    @State private var hostView: UIView?","","    var body: some View {","        VStack {","            Button(\"Show HUD\") {","                guard let view = hostView else { return }","                HUD.show(to: view, mode: .indicator(), label: \"Loading...\")","            }","            Button(\"Hide HUD\") {","                guard let view = hostView else { return }","                HUD.hide(for: view)","            }","        }","        .hudHost($hostView)","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This pattern gives you full access to the HUD instance and all configuration options.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Layer 2: Declarative Modifiers","level":2,"anchor":"Layer-2-Declarative-Modifiers","type":"heading"},{"text":"Boolean-Driven HUD","level":3,"anchor":"Boolean-Driven-HUD","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Toggle a HUD by binding a Boolean:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct DownloadView: View {","    @State private var isLoading = false","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Download\") {","            isLoading = true","            startDownload { isLoading = false }","        }","        .hud(isPresented: $isLoading) { hud in","            hud.contentView.mode = .indicator()","            hud.contentView.label.text = \"Downloading...\"","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Item-Driven HUD","level":3,"anchor":"Item-Driven-HUD","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Present different HUD states based on an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Identifiable"},{"text":" item:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct HUDItem: Identifiable {","    let id = UUID()","    let mode: ContentView.Mode","    let label: String","}","","struct TaskView: View {","    @State private var hudItem: HUDItem?","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Start\") {","            hudItem = HUDItem(mode: .indicator(), label: \"Working...\")","        }","        .hud(item: $hudItem) { item, hud in","            hud.contentView.mode = item.mode","            hud.contentView.label.text = item.label","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Self-Dismissing Status","level":3,"anchor":"Self-Dismissing-Status","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Show a toast that automatically hides after a duration:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct SaveView: View {","    @State private var showSaved = false","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Save\") {","            save()","            showSaved = true","        }","        .hudStatus(isPresented: $showSaved, duration: 2.0) { hud in","            hud.contentView.mode = .text","            hud.contentView.label.text = \"Saved!\"","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Layer 3: Convenience Presets","level":2,"anchor":"Layer-3-Convenience-Presets","type":"heading"},{"text":"Loading Indicator","level":3,"anchor":"Loading-Indicator","type":"heading"},{"code":["MyView()","    .hudLoading(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Please wait...\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Toast Message","level":3,"anchor":"Toast-Message","type":"heading"},{"code":["MyView()","    .hudToast(isPresented: $showToast, duration: 1.5, label: \"File deleted\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Progress Tracking","level":3,"anchor":"Progress-Tracking","type":"heading"},{"code":["struct UploadView: View {","    @State private var isUploading = false","    @State private var progress: Float = 0","","    var body: some View {","        Button(\"Upload\") { startUpload() }","            .hudProgress(isPresented: $isUploading, progress: $progress, label: \"Uploading\")","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Layer 4: Liquid Glass (iOS 26+)","level":2,"anchor":"Layer-4-Liquid-Glass-iOS-26+","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On iOS 26 and later, use the glass style for a modern translucent appearance:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["MyView()","    .hudGlass(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Loading...\")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"code":".hudGlass()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is only available when compiling with Swift 6.2+ and targeting iOS 26.0 or tvOS 26.0."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside"},{"text":"Animation Customization","level":2,"anchor":"Animation-Customization","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All declarative modifiers accept an "},{"code":"animation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":[".hud(isPresented: $isLoading, animation: .init(.zoomInOut, damping: .default)) { hud in","    hud.contentView.mode = .indicator()","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Migration from UIKit Bridge","level":2,"anchor":"Migration-from-UIKit-Bridge","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you previously used a local "},{"code":"HUDHostView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" helper, you can now:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Replace "},{"code":"import FlyHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"code":"import FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remove your local "},{"code":"HUDHostView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"HUDContainerModifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"hudHost()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" definitions"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":".hudHost($hostView)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" API is now provided by the SDK"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For new code, prefer the declarative modifiers (Layer 2\/3) over "},{"code":".hudHost()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for cleaner state management."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Best Practices","level":2,"anchor":"Best-Practices","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"One HUD per view hierarchy","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Avoid attaching multiple "},{"code":".hud()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifiers to the same view. Use "},{"code":"item:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" variant for multiple states."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Set binding to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" on dismissal","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — The status modifier does this automatically, but for "},{"code":".hud(isPresented:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" you must reset the binding yourself."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Combine with "},{"code":"FlyIndicatorHUD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"code":"FlyProgressHUD","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":" — Custom styles work the same way; just pass them via the configuration closure.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prefer convenience presets"}]},{"text":" — Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudLoading()"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudToast()"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".hudProgress()"},{"text":" for common cases to reduce boilerplate.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use FlyHUD declaratively in SwiftUI with the "},{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" module.","type":"text"}],"references":{"swiftui-architecture.svg":{"type":"image","alt":"Architecture diagram showing the four API layers of FlyHUDSwiftUI and their relationships to internal components and FlyHUD core","identifier":"swiftui-architecture.svg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/swiftui-architecture.svg","traits":["1x","light"],"svgID":"my-svg"}]},"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/best-practices":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Recommended patterns for using FlyHUD effectively in production apps."}],"role":"article","title":"Best Practices","url":"\/documentation\/flyhud\/best-practices","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/best-practices","kind":"article"},"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/advanced-features":{"abstract":[{"text":"Explore keyboard tracking, animations, grace time, activity counts, and more.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/flyhud\/advanced-features","title":"Advanced Features","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/advanced-features","kind":"article"},"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/testing":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategies for unit testing, integration testing, and mocking FlyHUD in your app."}],"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/testing","title":"Testing Guide","url":"\/documentation\/flyhud\/testing"},"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD":{"abstract":[{"text":"A lightweight and easy-to-use HUD for displaying progress and status of ongoing tasks on iOS, tvOS, and visionOS.","type":"text"}],"role":"collection","title":"FlyHUD","url":"\/documentation\/flyhud","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD","kind":"symbol"},"doc://flyhud.FlyHUD/documentation/FlyHUD/custom-ui":{"abstract":[{"text":"Build custom activity indicators, progress views, and display modes.","type":"text"}],"role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/flyhud\/custom-ui","title":"Custom UI","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/custom-ui","kind":"article"},"swiftui-bridge.svg":{"type":"image","alt":"Sequence diagram showing how SwiftUI binding changes flow through HUDModifier, HUDRepresentable, and HUDCoordinator to control HUD visibility","identifier":"swiftui-bridge.svg","variants":[{"url":"\/i